node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Business & Entrepreneur on July 22, 2021 tagging @richardyuzee. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Richard Yu @richardyuzee 6 life-changing habits that made me a millionaire at 22 (A thread)'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on July 22, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Richard Yu @richardyuzee 1. Deep Work have 3 hours UNDISTRACTED work every day of No social media, no email, no phone. Staying focused and removing distractions is key if you want to accomplish more.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on July 22, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Richard Yu @richardyuzee 2. Wake Wake up and go to bed at the same time every day It increases your energy evels builds discipline. and I've woken woken up at 5 AM and slept at9 at PM 6 days out of the week for the past 5-6 years.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on July 22, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Richard Yu @richardyuzee 3. Delayed gratification too much partying, TV shows, video games, unhealthy food, etc will ruin your motivation. Work hard now and make short term sacrifices for your long term goal and the future life you want.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on July 22, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Richard Yu @richardyuzee 4. Work out MINIMUM 3 times a week to train your body, but more importantly, train your mind. Exercising regularly builds discipline, resilience and increases your energy. The key is to be consistent with it.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on July 22, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Richard Yu @richardyuzee 5. How you do one thing is how you do everything If you don't give 100% to your workouts, you're not going to give 100% to your business. Treat everything with excellence and see how your life changes.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on July 22, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Richard Yu @richardyuzee 6. Practice gratitude. Take time to give thanks eeery day. pray to God and thank him daily for the life and opportunity He's given me.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on July 22, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Richard Yu @richardyuzee Remember, the quality of your future future depends on your daily habits. If you want to change your life, start by changing your habits.'.

node.text:
Where do billionaire entrepreneurs come from? Sometimes it’s an attic in Kansas City. That’s where Scott Lynn started his first business Virtumundo (later renamed Treeloot) when he was 15 years old. It quickly became the most popular game and one of the largest advertisers on the Internet in the late 90s.

Later, Scott founded Adknowledge, which became the fourth largest digital advertising marketplace behind Google, Yahoo and MSN. A lifelong entrepreneur, he continued to found a series of technology companies which have been valued at over $1 billion.

Throughout all these pursuits and changes in his life, there was one thing he kept constant: his passion for art. Inspired by his mother, who was an art teacher, he became one of the top art collectors in the world. His passion has made good business sense: contemporary art prices outpaced the S&P 500 total return almost two-fold over the same period, according to data compiled from public sources.

Contemporary art is an asset, so why can’t the typical investor access it? Real estate, gold, and other alternatives have been securitized, so why not art?

Now, Scott spends his days on the top floor of his New York office for his new company, Masterworks, that lets you invest through fractional ownership. The platform already has over 180,000 registered users of all types from around the globe.

His sole first exit returned 32% net to investors, and he’s just getting started. What’s your twenty-year story? Comment below and check the link in our bio to learn more about Masterworks and skip their waitlist.
-
@masterworks.io
